1
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,680
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

2
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,520
YUXI CIGARETTE

3
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:09,639
Stop looking.

4
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:11,920
He is not coming.

5
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,840
You should just come with me
to the cement factory.

6
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,400
Let's wait a bit longer.

7
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:17,120
He told the property management
on the phone

8
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,040
that he would come in person.

9
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:23,040
Trying to deal with someone like
Song Qingsong, you are still too green.

10
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,680
Just this bag of stuff.

11
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:27,440
It means nothing to him.

12
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:31,000
- Why would he come?
- What if he feels guilty?

13
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:33,240
What if there's something at home
he doesn't want anyone

14
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,560
or the police to find?

15
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,600
I think the one feeling guilty is you.

16
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:44,160
Keep staring, and you will turn
into Meng Jiangnv.

17
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:53,560
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY, WEIYANG CITY

18
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,360
What are you doing?

19
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,440
That guy dared to harm Wolf.
I am going to cripple him.

20
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,400
Do you even have a brain?

21
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:13,000
Did you forget we have transformed?

22
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:15,280
Still talking about knives and guns?
Put it away.

23
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,960
Mr. Jin, you said it yourself,
we were going to deal with him.

24
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:21,760
Do you know who owns that car
with plate 688?

25
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:24,120
The boss of Qingsong Cement Factory,

26
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,640
Song Qingsong.

27
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:28,160
How many lives do you think
you have to mess with him?

28
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:30,320
So we are not avenging Wolf?

29
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:33,280
We need to figure out the situation first
before we take revenge.

30
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:36,840
How did Song Qingsong
get involved with Manlang?

31
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:38,120
Alright.

32
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:40,080
That makes sense.

33
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,520
Follow him.

34
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,200
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY, WEIYANG CITY

35
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:19,519
If any words Song Qingsong said were true,

36
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:23,880
every pig in Weiyang
would be climbing trees.

37
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:17,680
Criminal Department.

38
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:19,080
<i>A Mercedes just arrived at the entrance.</i>

39
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,600
<i>They say they are</i>
<i>the owner from Yuanlongli.</i>

40
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,720
Let them in.

41
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:27,400
- Brigade meeting room.
- <i>Got it.</i>

42
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:36,480
Come on. We'll be seeing pigs climb trees.

43
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:43,040
Hey.

44
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,120
Why the rush?

45
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,560
Have you figured out
how to question him about Xu Meng?

46
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:49,240
Go through every detail
and verify everything.

47
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:52,000
As long as there are inconsistencies,
we will find a breakthrough.

48
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:56,120
Song Qingsong
is the victim, not a suspect.

49
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:58,840
What if he just takes his stuff
and leaves without saying anything?

50
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,720
Tell me, what will you do then?

51
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,320
So what is your plan?

52
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,080
Very simple. Five words.

53
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,480
We will work in tandem.

54
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,840
How?

55
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,000
I lead, you back me up.

56
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,080
I ease him in, you pin him down.

57
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,160
I play the good cop, you play the bad cop.

58
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,080
Got it?

59
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,680
Are you sure
that's really your real intention?

60
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,280
Just tell me. Do you get it or not?

61
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,160
SPECIAL TASK FORCE

62
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,080
The good cop goes first.

63
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:57,480
What is Song Qingsong
doing at the police station?

64
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:00,640
Could the police have traced
the Wolf case back to him?

65
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:02,280
Trace, my foot.

66
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,800
If they had, he'd be here in a police car.

67
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:04,880
Right.

68
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,520
You just reminded me.

69
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:12,080
If Song Qingsong
really had dealings with Manlang,

70
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,960
- then we could…
- We can squeeze him for a big payout.

71
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,200
Squeeze your head.

72
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:18,880
Jeez. We need to think differently.

73
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:22,600
Use this opportunity
to talk to Song Qingsong.

74
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:24,720
Get him to throw us some business.

75
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:29,200
That's called "Water flows downhill,
people move up."

76
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,800
Move up?

77
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:33,600
What Song Qingsong did before
was way worse than what we did.

78
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,600
I…

79
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:37,160
If someone like him can clean up his act,

80
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:40,800
then I should learn from him.

81
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:53,520
ID and letter of introduction are fine.

82
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,680
This tea tastes terrible.

83
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,760
Wait.

84
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:05,880
The owner has to come in person
to claim the stolen items.

85
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:07,160
Call Song Qingsong.

86
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,640
Have him come himself.

87
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:12,040
Officer,
I have already made it very clear.

88
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:15,640
The house belongs to my brother-in-law,
but I have been living there recently.

89
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:18,400
So everything in the safe belongs to me.

90
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:22,480
Alright. Let's verify everything,
one by one.

91
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:24,160
What do you mean?

92
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,760
Where were you earlier?

93
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:29,360
By procedure, we need to confirm
in person that the items are yours

94
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:31,040
before you can take them.

95
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:36,080
Please go ahead.

96
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:44,120
What brand is the liquor?
How many bottles?

97
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:47,040
Moutai. 53-degree Feitian.

98
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,120
- Four bottles.
- Cigarettes?

99
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,240
Zhonghua. Four cartons.

100
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,080
Four cartons of Zhonghua.

101
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,880
- Yuxi.
- Two cartons.

102
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,560
Two cartons of Yuxi.

103
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:00,960
Flip-top Yuxi.

104
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,400
Belts?

105
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,320
Two belts.

106
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,040
One gold Rolex.

107
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,680
Three gold rings.

108
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,120
Five gold chains.

109
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,480
Two lighters.

110
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:15,800
Three bundles of cash.

111
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,040
Bring everything out.

112
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:19,240
How much cash?

113
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:25,760
Hundred-yuan bills.
Three bundles. Ten thousand each.

114
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:28,080
That makes 30,000.

115
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,440
He.

116
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:37,320
That number sounds familiar.

117
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,440
Yeah, it does.

118
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:41,240
I heard there's a rule on the street.

119
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:45,320
Say it's a 40,000-yuan job,
you pay 10,000 upfront,

120
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:48,480
then the remaining 30 after it's done.

121
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:50,240
And there's usually a little bonus, right?

122
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,640
At least

123
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:55,320
two cartons of flip-top Yuxi.

124
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:04,560
Keep going.

125
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:06,560
I don't have all day.

126
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,080
Have you checked everything?

127
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:09,040
Can I go now?

128
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,760
Darn it.

129
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,080
My watch… Where is my gold Rolex?
Where is the money?

130
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:32,000
- Where is my briefcase?
- What briefcase?

131
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,440
Briefcase… There is no briefcase.

132
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:37,680
You remembered it wrong.

133
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:38,840
I am a bit confused.

134
00:10:39,560 --> 00:10:41,200
I have been here too long.

135
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,400
You mean Song Qingsong's briefcase?

136
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,840
No, no. I remembered it wrong.
There wasn't one.

137
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:54,040
It had "Qingsong Cement"
written on it, right?

138
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,160
I remembered it wrong.

139
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:56,320
Something in that bag you don't want seen?

140
00:10:56,400 --> 00:11:00,040
Call Song Qingsong.
Tell him the briefcase is missing.

141
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,440
<i>Take the items.</i>

142
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:07,720
<i>Get to Dahuihuang now.</i>

143
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:12,640
I still have work.
Is it done now? Can I leave?

144
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:16,160
Are you sure that's everything?
Nothing else? A watch?

145
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,720
- Cash?
- I am sure.

146
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:20,000
That is all.

147
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:42,760
"Build strength."

148
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:44,680
What is that?

149
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:46,960
"Forge the police…"

150
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,320
What is that?

151
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:53,880
"Build strength, forge the police soul."

152
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,040
You don't recognize the "soul" character?

153
00:11:59,120 --> 00:12:00,720
What does it mean?

154
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:03,560
Those two characters look a bit creepy.

155
00:12:05,680 --> 00:12:07,400
It has two meanings.

156
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:11,800
One is ghost, the other is spirit.

157
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:13,360
- Got it?
- Got it.

158
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:15,040
I have plenty of spirit.

159
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:17,680
Whose kid are you?

160
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:20,160
My dad is He Yuanhang.

161
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:23,280
That Officer He on secondment.
I have heard of him.

162
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:25,280
Miss, I need to use the restroom.

163
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,720
Do you know where it is?

164
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,520
Yes. I will take you.

165
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,240
Let's go.

166
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,360
Xiaohe.

167
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,600
Your shoelace is undone. Let me tie it.

168
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,000
Miss, he is looking at your waist.

169
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:50,560
- Don't go. You're a bad guy.
- Hey.

170
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:52,240
Kid, you're mistaken.

171
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:55,920
- Mistaken? Kids don't lie.
- Dad, there's a pervert here!

172
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,960
- What have you done?
- What is going on?

173
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:03,440
Let go. Is this your child?

174
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:05,600
None of your business.
Sharp face. Dark circles.

175
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:08,200
You look kind of creepy.

176
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:09,400
Like a pervert.

177
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:14,040
At such a young age,
your temper is already this bad.

178
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,840
You'd better watch yourself
when you grow up.

179
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:18,080
- Hey!
- I am just telling the truth.

180
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:19,880
You do need to be careful out there.

181
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:27,520
He,

182
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:30,640
when we mentioned the briefcase,
his eyes went right.

183
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:32,800
When we mentioned the cash,
they shifted left.

184
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:35,920
He was lying about the briefcase,

185
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,160
but the 30,000 in cash,
he was recalling it.

186
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:42,320
The one who hired someone
is very likely him.

187
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:46,520
He should be on his way now
to find Song Qingsong.

188
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,600
Song Qingsong.

189
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:50,840
Officer He,

190
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:54,280
if you're going out, leave Xiaohe with me.

191
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,840
I'm Liang Juan from the Analysis Unit.

192
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:58,480
I'm on the night shift. I can take her
to the cafeteria later.

193
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:06,920
Thank you, Officer Liang.

194
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,280
- Not at all.
- Kiddo,

195
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:09,840
I'll come back to pick you up later.

196
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:11,880
- Listen to Ms. Liang, alright?
- Okay.

197
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:17,040
So you are the new top graduate
in the Criminal Department.

198
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:18,920
He is.

199
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:20,840
Hello.

200
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,880
You two work well together.

201
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:24,680
Right, Xiaohe?

202
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:28,160
Let's go.

203
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:30,680
He's out.

204
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:34,800
Wait.

205
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:37,800
He Yuanhang.

206
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:41,600
The cops are following him.
Should we still follow?

207
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,360
Yes.

208
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:18,480
He, just the Yuxi cigarettes
and Wu Shanlong's reactions aren't enough.

209
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:20,720
Even if we follow him
and find Song Qingsong,

210
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:22,520
we need a plan first.

211
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:24,280
What plan?

212
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,720
Get him back to the station first,
no matter what.

213
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:31,120
What? Even a top graduate like you
consults me now?

214
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:38,280
I have noticed your methods
can be quite effective at times.

215
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,440
There are only three days left.

216
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:41,880
If we don't use some tactics,
we won't get anywhere.

217
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:43,960
This missing persons case looks simple,

218
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:45,680
but the deeper we dig,
the more complicated it gets.

219
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,280
It is like a maze.

220
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:49,360
A maze?

221
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:54,320
I do have a theory for that.
Trémaux's algorithm.

222
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:56,600
Don't even start. My head is spinning.

223
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:14,000
Is it funny?

224
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,320
Come on. You sing. Go on. Just sing.

225
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,480
‪Come on, sing it!

226
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,120
Sing.

227
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:35,480
- Director Li.
- <i>Song Qingsong.</i>

228
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:36,960
What's your order?

229
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:38,920
<i>Where are you?</i>

230
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:41,480
- At the factory.
- <i>At the factory?</i>

231
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:43,880
<i>Do you know about the mine break-in?</i>

232
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:44,800
No.

233
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:50,960
Well, I just got back
from a business trip.

234
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:55,960
Are the documents still there?

235
00:16:56,040 --> 00:16:58,160
<i>Still there? They have all been taken.</i>

236
00:16:58,240 --> 00:16:59,840
<i>The police are involved now.</i>

237
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:01,960
<i>I've been told to issue a statement</i>
<i>declaring all the stolen documents</i>

238
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:03,120
<i>null and void.</i>

239
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,319
<i>Yours too.</i>

240
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:08,079
Director Li, the documents may be voided,

241
00:17:08,599 --> 00:17:10,720
but my money isn't, right?

242
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,440
<i>Are you out of your mind?</i>

243
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:13,760
<i>Talking about this on the phone?</i>

244
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,880
Was the mine really robbed?

245
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:18,760
- Or was it…
- <i>Enough.</i>

246
00:17:18,839 --> 00:17:22,000
<i>Cut the crap. Burn the documents now.</i>

247
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:24,440
<i>If anyone sees them, it's on you.</i>

248
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,119
<i>Do you hear me?</i>

249
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:27,880
<i>Hello?</i>

250
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,280
- Again.
- <i>Song Qingsong.</i>

251
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,080
- Another one.
- <i>Do you hear me?</i>

252
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:32,600
Trying to set me up.

253
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:42,240
Mr. Liu, where are you now?

254
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:44,720
Here's the situation.

255
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:47,360
Something just came up on my end.

256
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:50,320
My driver lost the documents.

257
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:53,600
When you arrive, we'll talk…

258
00:17:54,520 --> 00:17:55,720
Liu?

259
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:57,440
Hello?

260
00:17:58,560 --> 00:17:59,800
Hello?

261
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:15,320
DAHUIHUANG NIGHTCLUB

262
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:40,760
That fool Song Qingsong is not in the car.

263
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:43,640
Then who is this idiot?

264
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,880
Welcome, boss.
We are glad to have you here.

265
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:56,080
Wasn't it plate 688?

266
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,720
You sure?

267
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:59,040
I'm sure.

268
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:07,360
Mr. Jin, I know someone
who'll remember it better than me.

269
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:16,440
He.

270
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:19,440
- He.
- What?

271
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:23,120
We are just walking in like this?

272
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:26,000
If not, are we supposed to climb in?

273
00:19:27,920 --> 00:19:29,520
You've done raids here before, have you?

274
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:32,520
Even if I have, it doesn't stop you
from investigating.

275
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:39,160
What I mean is,

276
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:41,800
should we

277
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:44,800
coordinate a bit?

278
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:49,760
You lead, I back you up.

279
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:51,800
You play one role, I play the other.

280
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:52,760
That one.

281
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:56,280
This time, you're the one asking me.

282
00:19:58,320 --> 00:20:00,520
What do you mean by "asking"?

283
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,280
We're partners.

284
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:03,800
Exactly.

285
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:06,960
On a case, you have to lower yourself
and act naturally.

286
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:08,320
Let's go.

287
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:16,320
Welcome, boss.
We are glad to have you here.

288
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:18,920
Police. Get Ms. Xia over.

289
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,160
Alright.

290
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:33,640
Mr. Song, I brought it.

291
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:36,360
Now?

292
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:39,000
What's the point now?

293
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:40,480
No, but…

294
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:41,480
I brought it.

295
00:20:42,360 --> 00:20:45,920
Eight million, and I ended up
with a pile of scrap! Scrap!

296
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:49,560
Li, you are dead.

297
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:52,520
Officer He.

298
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:55,480
Officer He, what brings you here today?

299
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:56,440
Checking up on us?

300
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:59,520
Don't worry.
We're running things legally now.

301
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:00,760
We won't break the rules.

302
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:03,920
You said that last time.
And the time before.

303
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:06,120
We have been making improvements.

304
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:10,200
Let me ask you,
which room is Song Qingsong in?

305
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:13,240
What Song Qingsong?

306
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:14,600
Never heard of him.

307
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,120
What about Wu Shanlong?

308
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,320
Which room is Wu Shanlong in?

309
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:22,480
Officer He, I don't know who they are.

310
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:24,320
I've never heard of their names.

311
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:28,280
Ran, make a call.
Get the Public Order Unit over here.

312
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:35,280
Okay. Maybe we should also call
the fire, commerce, and tax too.

313
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:36,960
- We should call them all.
- Good idea. Call them all.

314
00:21:37,040 --> 00:21:39,480
- Alright.
- No need.

315
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:42,640
There's no need to make a fuss over this.
Everyone is tired, right?

316
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:45,280
Oh my goodness.

317
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:49,440
What are you still doing here?

318
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:51,520
Get lost!

319
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:57,280
Mr. Song, getting angry
is bad for your health.

320
00:21:57,360 --> 00:21:58,720
Who the heck are you?

321
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:01,880
Mr. Song, they're police.

322
00:22:05,560 --> 00:22:07,680
I'm He Yuanhang from the Nanshan Branch.

323
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:11,040
I just got off work.
So I brought a colleague out to relax.

324
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:14,080
We heard you were here,
so we came by to pay a visit.

325
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:16,360
I cannot stand the cops. Get out.

326
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:18,640
Song Qingsong, we have received a report

327
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:21,040
that you solicited prostitution
at Dahuihuang.

328
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:25,480
Who is making
false accusations against me?

329
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:28,120
This briefcase contains
the payment, does it not?

330
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:34,560
The things inside the briefcase
are important documents

331
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:36,680
from the cement factory.
They're confidential.

332
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:39,320
Without a warrant,
no one is allowed to touch it.

333
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,040
I will call my superiors right now.

334
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:43,040
It is a misunderstanding.

335
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:44,640
It must be.

336
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:47,120
How could Mr. Song
possibly do such a thing?

337
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:50,280
Right, I almost forgot.

338
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:52,240
I have something here
for you to take a look at.

339
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:54,080
Do you know this woman?

340
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:55,600
I do not.

341
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:57,280
Let me remind you.

342
00:22:57,360 --> 00:22:59,120
Muse Foot Massage. Mengmeng.

343
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:01,720
Just last week, you hit her.

344
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:03,000
Nonsense.

345
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,800
I never hit women.

346
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:06,320
Do you have any evidence?

347
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:07,880
If you have none, get lost.

348
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:12,320
Mr. Wu,

349
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:14,800
we didn't get a chance to thank you.

350
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:17,920
If you hadn't led the way,
how would we have met Mr. Song?

351
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:21,200
Mr. Song, they came on their own.

352
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,680
You went to the station yourself
to claim the lost items, right?

353
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:26,600
You said your brother-in-law,
Mr. Song, has treated you well,

354
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:28,680
so why are you still raking in so much?

355
00:23:28,760 --> 00:23:33,240
Moutai, Zhonghua, a gold Rolex,
and gold chains.

356
00:23:33,320 --> 00:23:34,360
That's over a hundred thousand.

357
00:23:34,440 --> 00:23:36,560
Nonsense. You're slandering me!

358
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:39,640
Mr. Wu,
you have been very cooperative today.

359
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:42,280
You told the Criminal Department
a lot about Mr. Song,

360
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:44,320
especially about that briefcase.

361
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:46,560
We had no idea it meant so much to him.

362
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:48,400
Even when Mengmeng merely touched it,

363
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:50,520
he made sure she disappeared from Weiyang.

364
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:51,920
You're framing me! Nonsense!

365
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:53,800
Bastard!

366
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:55,240
- You bastard!
- You let go!

367
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:56,360
Qingsong!

368
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:58,520
- If he goes too far, arrest him.
- They are…

369
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:01,080
They are clearly trying to drive
a wedge between us.

370
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:06,200
Assaulting police officers is a crime.

371
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:12,720
The police are hitting me!

372
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:20,640
- Qingsong, run!
- Stop right there.

373
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:22,320
- Let go.
- Qingsong, run!

374
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:23,520
- Stop.
- Qingsong.

375
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:24,520
Vice squad!

376
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:28,080
Vice squad!

377
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:31,640
Vice squad!

378
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:34,680
- Run!
- Vice raid! Run!

379
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:40,760
‪Hurry! Run!

380
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:43,600
Is that him? Right?

381
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:45,360
- No. Not him.
- Is that him?

382
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:49,720
This way.

383
00:24:51,560 --> 00:24:52,640
Leave now!

384
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:05,080
Mr. Jin.

385
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:06,600
The one who climbed down the pipe.

386
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:08,640
That is him! That is him!

387
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:13,640
You still recognize him
with that injury on his head?

388
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:15,720
Mr. Jin, I never forget a face.

389
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:17,840
- Bring him here. Hurry.
- Alright.

390
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:20,680
DAHUIHUANG NIGHTCLUB

391
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:26,400
- He, drive.
- Mr. Jin.

392
00:25:27,080 --> 00:25:28,080
Police.

393
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:32,400
Fuck.

394
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:33,960
One after another.

395
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:35,560
What is this, Snake?

396
00:25:38,760 --> 00:25:40,080
Behind us.

397
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:56,880
Son of a bitch!

398
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:15,240
Faster. Go faster.

399
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:17,160
This is just a Fukang.
He's driving a Benz.

400
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:19,600
If Song Qingsong gets away this time,
it will be hard to find him again.

401
00:26:42,040 --> 00:26:44,920
Song Qingsong,
I will not let you get away.

402
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:47,000
He, don't lose your head. Be careful.

403
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:49,720
At this point, whoever eases off loses.

404
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:52,280
He's cutting me off.
Then I'll cut him off too.

405
00:26:52,360 --> 00:26:55,160
If there's an accident,
we'll bring both him and the car in.

406
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:56,600
That works.

407
00:26:58,880 --> 00:27:00,440
He, accelerate.

408
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:35,760
Benz, here I come.

409
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:48,880
Come on.

410
00:27:54,280 --> 00:27:55,440
It won't move?

411
00:27:56,080 --> 00:27:57,280
Hurry up.

412
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:58,440
- I can't move it!
- They're gone.

413
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:13,440
Song Qingsong, you scoundrel!

414
00:28:13,520 --> 00:28:15,720
You wrecked my car. I'm not done with you!

415
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:24,520
<i>Wu Shanlong,</i>
<i>didn't you say it was in the safe?</i>

416
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:27,040
<i>What a coincidence</i>
<i>that the thief just happened to take it.</i>

417
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:29,520
<i>Wu Shanlong, are you playing me?</i>

418
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:33,160
Stop yelling at me.

419
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:35,040
Everyone has been yelling at me today.

420
00:28:36,040 --> 00:28:37,760
I'm telling you,
even if we got the documents,

421
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:38,960
they're useless now.

422
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:40,560
<i>Useless?</i>

423
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:42,160
<i>What do you mean? Explain.</i>

424
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:45,040
Dongshan Mine was robbed.
You know that, right?

425
00:28:45,120 --> 00:28:46,280
The bidding documents were inside.

426
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:48,760
Song Qingsong is furious.

427
00:28:48,840 --> 00:28:50,800
He spent eight million
on a pile of worthless paper.

428
00:28:50,880 --> 00:28:54,320
You want to blackmail him
with that pile of worthless paper?

429
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:02,200
The police came just now.

430
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:07,000
They seem to be onto Mengmeng.

431
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:10,760
If Song Qingsong gets arrested,

432
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:12,680
neither of us is getting out of this.

433
00:29:14,320 --> 00:29:15,600
What do we do now?

434
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:18,200
<i>I know what to do.</i>

435
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:22,680
Hello?

436
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:25,120
Hello?

437
00:29:55,640 --> 00:30:01,520
QINGSONG CEMENT

438
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:08,600
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

439
00:30:13,080 --> 00:30:14,080
SPECIAL TASK FORCE MEMBER LIST

440
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:16,760
- Xiaohe.
- Xiaohe.

441
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:18,240
What major case is it this time?

442
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:19,920
Four teenagers went missing
in Binchuan District.

443
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:20,840
They still have not been found.

444
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:22,680
Now the municipal bureau
is forming a special task force.

445
00:30:22,760 --> 00:30:23,920
Our district has to assist.

446
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,080
Didn't they call you to join?

447
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:28,320
Enough chatting. Meeting.

448
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:30,960
We will go up first.

449
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:42,960
Xiaohe, you're finally here.

450
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:44,480
Captain Zhao has been looking for you.

451
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:45,800
- For me?
- Go on.

452
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,760
APPROVED

453
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:54,120
- Captain Zhao.
- Come in.

454
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:55,360
APPROVED BY ZHAO JIE

455
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:58,600
Sit.

456
00:31:02,800 --> 00:31:03,920
Xiaohe,

457
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:07,680
about Han Zi'ang's case,
I plan to assign it to you.

458
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:09,320
Han Zi'ang's case?

459
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,480
What about the one in Binchuan District?

460
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:17,000
What, you think
this case isn't big enough?

461
00:31:18,480 --> 00:31:20,880
Of course not.
I wouldn't dare pick and choose.

462
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:22,720
Captain, don't worry.

463
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,560
I will make sure this case
is thoroughly investigated.

464
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:27,680
About this case, Captain Qu
wrote a report yesterday.

465
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:29,080
You can refer to it.

466
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:30,080
Okay.

467
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:32,760
From what we can tell,
it's most likely a prank.

468
00:31:32,840 --> 00:31:35,680
So, the focus is on cleanup
and calming the parents.

469
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:36,920
Understood?

470
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:41,080
CAPTAIN'S OFFICE

471
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:50,040
One more thing.

472
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:52,960
Sort out your family matters
as soon as possible.

473
00:32:04,800 --> 00:32:06,520
See? I told you.

474
00:32:07,040 --> 00:32:08,440
By seniority,

475
00:32:08,520 --> 00:32:11,240
Zhao Jie is still just a kid to me.

476
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:14,920
He Yuanhang,
you should give up on that idea.

477
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:16,880
I will not let you,

478
00:32:18,120 --> 00:32:20,240
or any of you, get involved in this case.

479
00:32:21,320 --> 00:32:24,120
Just treat me and Mr. Ran as helpers.

480
00:32:24,200 --> 00:32:26,360
No need to feed us. We won't steal credit.

481
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:28,080
All upside.

482
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:30,960
If you keep causing trouble,
I'll transfer back to the archives

483
00:32:31,040 --> 00:32:32,720
- and sit there doing nothing.
- No, no.

484
00:32:34,080 --> 00:32:35,960
I'm begging you. Please.

485
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:38,600
Help Mr. Ran, okay?

486
00:32:38,680 --> 00:32:40,000
There is nothing I can do to help him.

487
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:42,720
He Xiaohe, that is Mr. Ran.

488
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:44,160
He watched you grow up.

489
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:46,000
Have you forgotten how good he was to you?

490
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:47,360
I have not.

491
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:49,680
He's doing quite well now.

492
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,760
Stop bothering him.
It's not good for either of you.

493
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:56,520
He's just pretending he's fine.

494
00:32:57,160 --> 00:33:00,200
Since I came back, I have looked into it.

495
00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:03,200
I found that he's still avoiding
that case from back then.

496
00:33:03,800 --> 00:33:05,160
It's his demon.

497
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:08,160
We need to help him face it.

498
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:09,960
- Face it?
- Right.

499
00:33:10,040 --> 00:33:12,440
- And then?
- Then,

500
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:16,400
he stays in Weiyang
and rejoins the Criminal Department.

501
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:18,320
You're dreaming again.

502
00:33:18,400 --> 00:33:19,760
He's a university lecturer now.

503
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:22,040
Can he just be transferred back
to the Criminal Department?

504
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:24,840
Besides, he's doing great in Beijing.

505
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:27,200
Why do you insist
on bringing him back to Weiyang?

506
00:33:27,280 --> 00:33:28,960
That's for later.

507
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:30,960
Right now, let's talk
about the helpers thing.

508
00:33:31,040 --> 00:33:32,880
I'll be honest with you.

509
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:36,400
Captain Zhao assigned this case
to me not because of you.

510
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:39,200
Everyone thinks it's a prank.
Barely even a case.

511
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:40,240
What?

512
00:33:41,600 --> 00:33:43,600
What kind of logic is that?

513
00:33:44,120 --> 00:33:46,480
Back when Xu Meng
and her father went missing,

514
00:33:46,560 --> 00:33:48,000
everyone said it was a prank too.

515
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:49,240
Was it?

516
00:33:54,640 --> 00:33:55,600
Dad,

517
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:58,600
stop dwelling on the past.

518
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:01,440
Go home.

519
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:03,680
I've got work.

520
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:06,880
Hey!

521
00:34:17,520 --> 00:34:24,520
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

522
00:34:32,080 --> 00:34:32,920
Master!

523
00:34:36,120 --> 00:34:37,760
Master, thank you.

524
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:39,600
Master, thank you.

525
00:34:39,679 --> 00:34:41,800
I really should have
listened to you yesterday

526
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:42,920
and gone straight to Yuanlongli.

527
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:45,639
Would've saved a lot of trouble.
Thank you so much.

528
00:34:45,719 --> 00:34:47,120
- Thank you.
- It's nothing.

529
00:34:47,199 --> 00:34:48,280
No big deal.

530
00:34:48,360 --> 00:34:49,400
How's your child?

531
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:51,440
He is still unconscious.

532
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:53,120
The police say he attacked
someone with a knife.

533
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:54,280
How is that possible?

534
00:34:54,360 --> 00:34:57,160
The school wants to expel him.

535
00:34:57,240 --> 00:35:00,400
I really don't know what to do.

536
00:35:01,920 --> 00:35:04,040
But he did attack someone.

537
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:06,600
Did anyone actually see it?

538
00:35:06,680 --> 00:35:08,440
Bring that person out
and let them face me.

539
00:35:08,520 --> 00:35:11,720
I want to see who it was
that knocked him unconscious.

540
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:13,640
Master,

541
00:35:14,720 --> 00:35:15,840
you are experienced.

542
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:17,240
Please do a reading for me.

543
00:35:17,320 --> 00:35:20,120
See whether my child
can get through this safely.

544
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:22,200
I don't do fortune-telling.

545
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:23,160
I only find people.

546
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:25,640
Then please help me find the culprit.

547
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:31,720
How about I find you an expert?
If he takes the case,

548
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:33,600
your child's situation will definitely
be thoroughly investigated.

549
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:34,720
I'll do whatever you say.

550
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:36,640
Wait here, I'll call him out.

551
00:35:37,160 --> 00:35:38,560
Thank you, Master. Thank you.

552
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:43,360
He really is remarkable.

553
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:04,480
Hurry up. The mother is waiting.

554
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:07,040
Move it.

555
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:10,000
You're so careless.

556
00:36:15,520 --> 00:36:17,880
Ms. Wang, I have been looking
for you. Get in the car.

557
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:20,760
Officer He, I'm waiting for someone.

558
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:23,040
Han Zi'ang's case is now under my charge.

559
00:36:23,120 --> 00:36:24,600
If you want to find out the truth,
come with me.

560
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:27,960
- But…
- Hurry, get in.

561
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:30,320
- Alright.
- Kiddo.

562
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:36,200
Kiddo.

563
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:55,640
Ms. Wang, don't worry too much
about your son's case.

564
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:58,520
The victim only has minor injuries.
It's considered a light offense.

565
00:36:59,120 --> 00:37:00,240
Trust us.

566
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,240
We'll get to the truth.

567
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:07,400
Ang is innocent.

568
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:10,080
He's so young.

569
00:37:10,160 --> 00:37:14,160
If he grows up carrying that,
what will people think of him?

570
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:17,960
He's in a private school now.

571
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:20,400
Look at me.

572
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:25,560
I pulled strings and spent
a lot of money to get him in.

573
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:29,480
If he gets expelled,

574
00:37:30,920 --> 00:37:33,840
our lives will be ruined.

575
00:37:37,080 --> 00:37:40,480
I'll go to the school tomorrow
and speak to the principal.

576
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:44,240
Thank you. Thank you, Officer.

577
00:37:44,320 --> 00:37:45,600
But I have one condition.

578
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:48,640
Go ahead.

579
00:37:49,880 --> 00:37:51,160
Stop seeing that old man.

580
00:37:53,120 --> 00:37:54,600
Master?

581
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:58,000
- Why?
- He's no master. He's my dad.

582
00:37:59,560 --> 00:38:00,960
He's a fraud.

583
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:03,440
You've got some nerve.

584
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:07,000
You tricked Song Qingsong?

585
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:11,440
You think someone like him
is that easy to trick?

586
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:13,720
He's suspicious.

587
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:16,840
Just a few looks
and you call him a suspect?

588
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:21,080
Where is the evidence? No evidence,
and now it's backfired on you.

589
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:25,760
The traffic police called me.

590
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:28,240
They said a Mercedes driver
reported you for rear-ending him.

591
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:30,040
He wants 30,000.

592
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:31,760
How much?

593
00:38:32,840 --> 00:38:33,720
Thirty thousand.

594
00:38:45,640 --> 00:38:47,040
- Done?
- Don't touch it.

595
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:48,200
It's not dry yet.

596
00:38:52,320 --> 00:38:53,920
I'm not letting this go
with Song Qingsong.

597
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:55,280
Keep an eye on Xiaohe.

598
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:56,520
I'm going to stake out the cement factory.

599
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:57,440
He.

600
00:38:58,760 --> 00:38:59,920
I was impulsive yesterday.

601
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,240
- I'm afraid…
- Afraid of what?

602
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:02,280
I'm not afraid of anyone.

603
00:39:03,680 --> 00:39:06,360
Dad, is that the bad guy who hit our car?

604
00:39:06,440 --> 00:39:08,320
I'm going too!

605
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:09,960
Kiddo, be good.

606
00:39:10,040 --> 00:39:12,960
Stay with Uncle Ran today.
I'll pick you up later.

607
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:16,600
Don't worry. I am not being impulsive.

608
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:17,920
I have to keep an eye on Song Qingsong.

609
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:19,720
- If not, he'll slip away.
- He.

610
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:24,240
If we can't get him soon,
we'll have no other leads.

611
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:26,920
I want to try that maze theory.

612
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:29,360
We've only got two days left.
Try whatever theory you've got.

613
00:39:29,440 --> 00:39:30,480
- I'm heading out.
- Hey!

614
00:39:31,080 --> 00:39:32,520
Be careful.

615
00:39:39,840 --> 00:39:42,560
Officer Ran,
this is Luandongzi's statement.

616
00:39:42,640 --> 00:39:44,480
- We need you to verify it.
- Thank you.

617
00:39:55,440 --> 00:39:57,480
QUESTION: HOW DID YOU GET IN YUANLONGLI?
ANSWER: YOU'VE CAME TO THE RIGHT PERSON

618
00:39:58,520 --> 00:40:00,440
There's an underground garage
at Yuanlongli?

619
00:40:00,520 --> 00:40:01,760
Yes.

620
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:03,600
Luandongzi said people who pass by there

621
00:40:03,680 --> 00:40:05,760
can avoid the cameras at
the security booth and building entrance.

622
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:11,040
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

623
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:42,640
Officer Ran,

624
00:40:42,720 --> 00:40:46,520
the entrance to this underground garage
was sealed a few years ago.

625
00:40:46,600 --> 00:40:49,920
There's only this small access door now.
You need a key.

626
00:40:50,840 --> 00:40:52,000
Where is the exit?

627
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:55,560
Outside the compound. Also needs a key.

628
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:58,080
Besides the property management,
who else has keys?

629
00:40:58,160 --> 00:40:59,320
Not sure.

630
00:40:59,400 --> 00:41:01,040
You'll have to ask Manager Qian.

631
00:41:05,400 --> 00:41:08,280
Officer Ran, I need to get back
to the CCTV room.

632
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:10,880
I'll leave you here.
All the keys for New York Block are here.

633
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:13,240
Return them to the property office
when you're done.

634
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:14,640
- Thank you.
- You are welcome.

635
00:41:14,720 --> 00:41:15,560
I'm heading off.

636
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:16,760
- Bye.
- Okay.

637
00:41:21,480 --> 00:41:22,400
Xiaohe.

638
00:41:24,680 --> 00:41:27,440
Uncle Ran,
this underground maze is so cool.

639
00:41:27,520 --> 00:41:29,200
Stay close.

640
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:31,160
There might be rats running out.

641
00:41:31,240 --> 00:41:33,080
I'm not afraid of rats.

642
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:36,240
I caught one this big at my grandma's.

643
00:41:57,560 --> 00:41:58,720
Xiaohe.

644
00:41:59,440 --> 00:42:00,320
Xiaohe.

645
00:42:01,480 --> 00:42:04,800
Uncle Ran. I caught a big rat!

646
00:42:04,880 --> 00:42:07,040
What are you doing? Let go!

647
00:42:07,680 --> 00:42:08,680
Who are you?

648
00:42:09,880 --> 00:42:11,920
- Stop shining that light!
- Manager Qian?

649
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:12,880
What are you doing here?

650
00:42:13,520 --> 00:42:16,600
Someone reported
that the motion lights are broken.

651
00:42:16,680 --> 00:42:17,800
I came to fix them.

652
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:18,880
SAFETY FIRST

653
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:24,120
Does an electrician's work
need the property manager to handle?

654
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:26,120
Oh, come on.

655
00:42:26,200 --> 00:42:28,080
Uncle Ran, don't believe him.

656
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:30,440
He looks more like a thief.

657
00:42:31,080 --> 00:42:32,440
Watch your mouth.

658
00:42:32,520 --> 00:42:34,240
Whose daughter are you?

659
00:42:34,320 --> 00:42:35,640
Officer He's daughter.

660
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:38,080
No wonder.

661
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:40,280
Your dad and I are good friends.

662
00:42:40,360 --> 00:42:42,400
You should be calling me Mr. Qian.

663
00:42:42,480 --> 00:42:45,480
Save it. I'm not friends with a thief.

664
00:42:45,560 --> 00:42:46,600
You!

665
00:42:50,840 --> 00:42:51,920
Officer Ran,

666
00:42:53,240 --> 00:42:55,560
what are you doing down here?

667
00:43:01,200 --> 00:43:02,720
Stop coughing.

668
00:43:02,800 --> 00:43:05,280
That penny-pincher
turned off the motion lights.

669
00:43:05,360 --> 00:43:07,680
- Why?
- To save electricity.

670
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:10,320
Tell me, what is he doing
with all that cement?

671
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:13,400
- Building a grave at home?
- You two!

672
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:15,760
Did you hear that?

673
00:43:15,840 --> 00:43:16,920
What was that sound?

674
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:19,120
Could it be those two missing people?

675
00:43:19,640 --> 00:43:20,480
Are you serious?

676
00:43:22,640 --> 00:43:24,160
You two!

677
00:43:25,600 --> 00:43:27,280
- Oh my goodness!
- Who is it?

678
00:43:27,360 --> 00:43:29,880
Don't scare me. I'm afraid of the dark!

679
00:43:35,440 --> 00:43:38,280
You two, get out here now!

680
00:43:39,440 --> 00:43:40,560
Why aren't you at work?

681
00:43:40,640 --> 00:43:43,080
What are you doing down here? For what?

682
00:43:43,160 --> 00:43:44,600
Didn't you tell us to…

683
00:43:44,680 --> 00:43:45,680
I… Tell…

684
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:47,240
Tell what?

685
00:43:47,320 --> 00:43:48,720
Get back to work!

686
00:43:53,080 --> 00:43:54,240
Wait.

687
00:43:57,560 --> 00:43:58,480
You dropped something.

688
00:44:09,520 --> 00:44:11,480
Officer Ran, I still have things
to do at the property office.

689
00:44:12,160 --> 00:44:13,680
I'll be heading up now too.

690
00:44:14,560 --> 00:44:15,600
Hold on.

691
00:44:19,360 --> 00:44:22,280
Besides the property management,
who else has the key to the garage?

692
00:44:25,320 --> 00:44:27,800
When Yuanlongli was first built,

693
00:44:28,320 --> 00:44:29,320
there weren't many cars.

694
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:31,080
The vehicle entrance was sealed off.

695
00:44:31,160 --> 00:44:33,720
At that time,
only the property management had the key.

696
00:44:33,800 --> 00:44:36,880
But then, later on,
the Pattia Club opened.

697
00:44:36,960 --> 00:44:38,680
They were afraid of resident complaints,

698
00:44:38,760 --> 00:44:41,520
so they had their guests
and staff use the garage.

699
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:43,600
The keys just couldn't be tracked anymore.

700
00:44:44,520 --> 00:44:45,400
Officer Ran,

701
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:49,840
- I… I'll be going…
- Just go. Mr. Penny-pincher.

702
00:44:52,720 --> 00:44:54,360
You really take after your dad.

703
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:36,880
SAFETY FIRST
